Consumer Complaint Analysis Dashboard

Overview:

This project analyzes 63K+ consumer complaints across financial products, issues, and submission channels.
The goal is to identify key problem areas and improve customer service performance using data-driven insights.

Objectives:
Identify top complaint issues and high-risk products
Analyze complaint trends over time
Evaluate response efficiency (timely response & resolution time)
Understand customer behavior across submission channels

Dataset:
Consumer complaint dataset (~63K records)
Includes fields: Product, Issue, State, Submitted Via, Response, Dates

Dashboards:
🔹 Dashboard 1: Executive Overview
Total Complaints, YTD, MoM Growth
Timely Response %, Avg Resolution Days
Complaint trends over time
Top products & states
Complaint status breakdown

🔹 Dashboard 2: Issue Analysis
Top 10 Customer Complaint Issues
Issues by Product
Complaints by Submission Channel
Avg Resolution Time by Product

Key Insights:
Managing an account is the most common complaint
Checking/Savings accounts generate the highest complaints
Most complaints are submitted via the Web channel
Some products (e.g., loans/mortgages) have longer resolution times

Tools & Skills Used
Power BI
DAX (KPIs, YTD, MoM Growth)
Data Modeling
Data Visualization
Interactive Filters (Slicers, Top N)

Business Impact:
Helps identify major customer pain points
Improves decision-making for service optimization
Supports faster complaint resolution strategies











